                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  \n      </td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n\n  \n  <h6 class=\"no-anchor\" id=\"returns\">Returns</h6>\n  <p><code>void</code></p>\n\n  \n\n\n  \n\n  \n</div>\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n    \n\n  \n\n  \n    </tbody>\n</table>\n\n  \n</section>\n\n\n\n  \n<section class=\"usage-notes\">\n  <h2 id=\"usage-notes\">Usage notes<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"api/ng-observable/InvokeSubject#usage-notes\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h2>\n  <p>Basic usage</p>\n<code-example language=\"ts\">\nconst subject = new <a href=\"api/ng-observable/InvokeSubject\" class=\"code-anchor\">InvokeSubject</a>&#x3C;string>() // single argument\nconst subject2 = new <a href=\"api/ng-observable/InvokeSubject\" class=\"code-anchor\">InvokeSubject</a>&#x3C;[string, number]>() // multiple arguments\n\nsubject(\"message\")\nsubject2(\"message\", 42)\n\n// with custom invoke function\nconst subject3 = new <a href=\"api/ng-observable/InvokeSubject\" class=\"code-anchor\">InvokeSubject</a>&#x3C;string>(function () {\n    subject3.next(\"message\") // call \"<a href=\"api/ng-observable/State#next\" class=\"code-anchor\">next</a>\" to emit value\n})\n</code-example>\n<p>Convert <code>@HostListener</code> and <code>(event)</code> bindings into observable streams</p>\n<code-example language=\"ts\">\n@Component({\n    template: `&#x3C;input type=\"text\" (input)=\"inputChanges($event)\" />`\n})\nexport class MyComponent implements OnDestroy {\n    @HostListener(\"click\", [\"$event\"])\n    readonly hostClick = new <a href=\"api/ng-observable/InvokeSubject\" class=\"code-anchor\">InvokeSubject</a>&#x3C;MouseEvent>()\n    readonly inputChanges = new <a href=\"api/ng-observable/InvokeSubject\" class=\"code-anchor\">InvokeSubject</a>&#x3C;Event>()\n\n    constructor() {\n        hostClick.subscribe(event => console.log(event))\n        inputChanges.subscribe(event => console.log(event))\n    }\n}\n</code-example>\n\n</section>\n\n\n\n  </div>\n</article>\n\n<!-- links to this doc:\n - api/ng-observable\n - guide/ng-observable\n-->\n<!-- links from this doc:\n - /api\n - api/ng-observable\n - api/ng-observable/InvokeSubject#call\n - api/ng-observable/InvokeSubject#call-signature\n - api/ng-observable/InvokeSubject#constructor\n - api/ng-observable/InvokeSubject#constructor()\n - api/ng-observable/InvokeSubject#invokesubject\n - api/ng-observable/InvokeSubject#methods\n - api/ng-observable/InvokeSubject#usage-notes\n - api/ng-observable/NextFn\n - api/ng-observable/State#next\n - https://github.com/zodiac-team/zodiac-ui/edit/master/libs/ng-observable/lib/invoke-subject.ts?message=docs(ng-observable)%3A%20describe%20your%20change...#L11-L76\n - https://github.com/zodiac-team/zodiac-ui/edit/master/libs/ng-observable/lib/invoke-subject.ts?message=docs(ng-observable)%3A%20describe%20your%20change...#L8-L8\n - https://github.com/zodiac-team/zodiac-ui/tree/master/libs/ng-observable/lib/invoke-subject.ts#L11-L76\n - https://github.com/zodiac-team/zodiac-ui/tree/master/libs/ng-observable/lib/invoke-subject.ts#L8-L8\n-->"
